@MinalMahalaShorthillsAI If we have 10,000 results and 100 `doc_id`, the current approach would run 100 queries to ES/DB, each retrieving 10,000 results, this creates significant load and inefficiency.

A better approach is to query once and process all `doc_id` in memory, reducing the number of queries and overall overhead.

An even more optimal solution is to include doc_id in the search criteria, allowing ES/DB to filter results directly. This leverages indexing and avoids fetching a large result set only to filter it afterward, significantly improving performance if search with `doc_id` supported.
